title: Sainz crash ends 3rd practice session in Russia
text:
Sainz crash ends 3rd practice session in Russia Associated Press 22 hrs ago SOCHI, Russia (AP) A heavy crash for Carlos Sainz Jr. ended the final practice session at the Russian Grand Prix on Saturday with the Toro Rosso driver hospitalized.
AdChoices Sainz lost control of his car on a high-speed stretch heading into a steep right-hand corner, before scraping along the wall and crashing head on into the barriers.
The Spanish driver remained in the car, with part of the barriers covering the cockpit as the medical car quickly attended. Cranes were used to lift the barrier sections off the car before Sainz was placed into an ambulance on a stretcher. He was conscious and moved his arms.
The session was red-flagged immediately after the crash with more than 20 minutes remaining and canceled shortly afterward.
Â© (AP Photo/Luca Bruno Ferrari driver Sebastian Vettel of Germany steers his car during the first free practice at the 'Sochi Autodrom' Formula One track , in Sochi, Russia, Friday, Oct. 9, 2015. The Formula one race will be held on Sunday. (AP Photo/Luca Bruno) Sainz's teammate Max Verstappen expressed concern over the radio to his team, asking ''Is he OK? It looked like a big one.'' The garage replied that ''We lost the power on the car, we don't know.''
Mercedes' Nico Rosberg set the fastest time of the session, ahead of Williams driver Valtteri Bottas and championship leader Lewis Hamilton of Mercedes.
